trans-unit.source: Returns an Array with all the elements in the collection for which the passed block returns true.
Returns an Array with all the elements in the collection that are not of the given type.
Returns an Array with all the elements in the collection that are of the given type.
Returns an Array with all the elements in the collection that match the RegExppattern.
Returns an Array with all the elements in the collection.
Returns an Array with chunks in the given size, eventually filled up with given value or nil.
Returns an Array with the first count elements in the collection.
Returns an Array with the first count elements removed from the original array.
Returns an Array with the first count elements removed from the original collection.
Returns an Array with the results of running the block against each element of the collection, removing nil values.
Returns an Array with the results of running the block against each element of the collection.
Returns an Int128 by invoking #to_i128! on value.
Returns an Int128 by invoking #to_i128 on value.
Returns an Int16 by invoking #to_i16! on value.
Returns an Int16 by invoking #to_i16 on value.
Returns an Int32 by invoking #to_i32! on value.
Returns an Int32 by invoking #to_i32 on value.
Returns an Int64 by invoking #to_i64! on value.
Returns an Int64 by invoking #to_i64 on value.
Returns an Int8 by invoking #to_i8! on value.
Returns an Int8 by invoking #to_i8 on value.
Returns an IPAddress matching this addrinfo.
Returns an Iterator for each codepoint.
Returns an Iterator for each index in self.
Returns an Iterator for the lines in this IO, where a line is defined by the arguments passed to this method, which can be the same ones as in the #gets methods.
Returns an Iterator for the bytes in this IO.
Returns an Iterator for the chars in this IO.
Returns an Iterator for the elements of self.
Returns an Iterator of Array(String) over a CSV's rows.
Returns an Iterator over each byte in the string.
Returns an Iterator over each character in the string.
Returns an Iterator over each possible permutation of size of self.
Returns an Iterator over the elements of self in reverse order.
Returns an Iterator over the elements of this range.
Returns an Iterator that cycles over the values of this range.
Returns an Iterator that returns each nth element in this range.
Returns an Iterator which yields each line of this string (see String#each_line).
Returns an UInt128 by invoking #to_u128! on value.
Returns an UInt128 by invoking #to_u128 on value.
Returns an UInt16 by invoking #to_u16! on value.
Returns an UInt16 by invoking #to_u16 on value.
Returns an UInt32 by invoking #to_u32! on value.
Returns an UInt32 by invoking #to_u32 on value.
Returns an UInt64 by invoking #to_u64! on value.
Returns an UInt64 by invoking #to_u64 on value.
Returns an UInt8 by invoking #to_u8! on value.
Returns an UInt8 by invoking #to_u8 on value.
Returns an Iterator that enumerates over the items, chunking them together based on the return value of the block.
Returns an absolute path to the executable file of the currently running program.

Returns an absolute path to the executable file of the currently running program. This is in opposition to PROGRAM_NAME which may be a relative or absolute path, just the executable file name or a symlink.
Returns an array containing all of the filenames except for . and .. in the given directory.
Returns an array containing all of the filenames in the given directory.
Returns an array of all files that match against any of patterns.
Returns an array of all the environment variable names.
Returns an array of all the environment variable values.
Returns an array of annotations with the given #type attached to this variable, or an empty ArrayLiteral if there are none.
Returns an array of annotations with the given type attached to this variable, or an empty ArrayLiteral if there are none.
Returns an array of tuples with key and values belonging to this Hash.
Returns an array of unnamed capture groups.
Returns an array with all the elements in the collection randomized using the given random number generator.
Returns an array with all the elements in the collection reversed.
Returns an array with each separate part of this path.
Returns an authorize URI from a given request token to redirect the user to obtain an access token, as specified by RFC 5849, Section 2.2.
Returns an empty HTTP::Params.
Returns an empty string.
Returns an integer derived from the boolean value, for interoperability with C-style booleans.
Returns an iterator for each chunked elements where elements are kept in a given chunk as long as the block's value over a pair of elements is truthy.
Returns an iterator for each chunked elements where the ends of chunks are defined by the block, when the block's value over a pair of elements is truthy.
Returns an iterator for each element of the set.
Returns an iterator over chunks of elements, where each chunk ends right after the given block's value is truthy.
Returns an iterator over chunks of elements, where each chunk ends right after the given pattern is matched with pattern === element.
Returns an iterator over chunks of elements, where each chunk ends right before the given block's value is truthy.
Returns an iterator over chunks of elements, where each chunk ends right before the given pattern is matched with pattern === element.
Returns an iterator over the cookies of this collection.
Returns an iterator over the hash entries.
Returns an iterator over the hash entries. Which behaves like an Iterator returning a Tuple consisting of the key and value types.
Returns an iterator over the hash keys.
Returns an iterator over the hash keys. Which behaves like an Iterator consisting of the key's types.
Returns an iterator over the hash values.
Returns an iterator over the hash values. Which behaves like an Iterator consisting of the value's types.
Returns an iterator over the parameter which behaves like an Iterator returning a Tuple of key and value.
Returns an iterator that applies the given block to the next element and returns the result.
Returns an iterator that applies the given function to the element and then returns it unless it is nil.
Returns an iterator that applies the given function to the element and then returns it unless it is nil. If the returned value would be nil it instead returns the next non nil value.
Returns an iterator that calls the given block with the next element of the iterator when calling #next, still returning the original element.
Returns an iterator that chunks the iterator's elements in arrays of size filling up the remaining elements if no element remains with nil or a given optional parameter.

Returns an iterator that flattens nested iterators and arrays into a single iterator whose type is the union of the simple types of all of the nested iterators and arrays (and their nested iterators and arrays, and so on).
Returns an iterator that only returns elements for which the passed in block returns a falsey value.
Returns an iterator that only returns elements for which the passed in block returns a truthy value.
Returns an iterator that only returns elements of the given type.
Returns an iterator that only returns elements that are not of the given type.
Returns an iterator that only returns elements where pattern === element does not hold.
Returns an iterator that only returns elements where pattern === element.
Returns an iterator that only returns every nth element, starting with the first.
Returns an iterator that only returns the first n elements of the initial iterator.
Returns an iterator that only returns unique values of the original iterator.
Returns an iterator that only returns unique values of the original iterator. The provided block is applied to the elements to determine the value to be checked for uniqueness.
Returns an iterator that only starts to return elements once the given block has returned falsey value for one element.
Returns an iterator that repeatedly returns the elements of the original iterator forever starting back at the beginning when the end was reached.
Returns an iterator that repeatedly returns the elements of the original iterator starting back at the beginning when the end was reached, but only n times.
Returns an iterator that returns a Tuple of the element and a given object.
Returns an iterator that returns a Tuple of the element and its index.
Returns an iterator that returns consecutive chunks of the size n.
Returns an iterator that returns elements from the original iterator until it is exhausted and then returns the elements of the second iterator.

Returns an iterator that returns elements from the original iterator until it is exhausted and then returns the elements of the second iterator. Compared to .chain(Iterator(Iter)), it has better performance when the quantity of iterators to chain is small (usually less than 4). This method also cannot chain iterators in a loop, for that see .chain(Iterator(Iter)).
Returns an iterator that returns elements while the given block returns a truthy value.
Returns an iterator that returns the elements of this iterator and the given one pairwise as Tuples.
Returns an iterator that skips the first n elements and only returns the elements after that.
Returns an iterator that then returns slices of n elements of the initial iterator.
Returns any backtrace associated with the exception if the call stack exists.
Returns any backtrace associated with the exception if the call stack exists. The backtrace is an array of strings, each containing “0xAddress: Function at File Line Column”.
Returns any backtrace associated with the exception.
Returns any backtrace associated with the exception. The backtrace is an array of strings, each containing “0xAddress: Function at File Line Column”.
Returns attribute count of the node.
Returns attributes of this node as an XML::Attributes.
Returns count or less (if there aren't enough) elements starting at the given start index.
Returns default options for parsing HTML documents.
Returns default options for parsing XML documents.
Returns detailed information for this node including node type, name, attributes and children.
Returns either an IPAddress or UNIXAddres from the internal OS representation.
Returns either an IPAddress or UNIXAddres from the internal OS representation. Only INET, INET6 and UNIX families are supported.
Returns first value for specified param name.
Returns first value for specified param name. Fallbacks to provided default value when there is no such param.
Returns first value for specified param name. Fallbacks to return value of provided block when there is no such param.
Returns first value for specified param name.
Returns first value or nil for specified param name.
Returns how many T elements are there between this pointer and other.
Returns how many T elements are there between this pointer and other. That is, this is (self.address - other.address) / sizeof(T).
Returns if among the headers for key there is some that contains word as a value.
Returns if among the headers for key there is some that contains word as a value. The word is expected to match between word boundaries (i.e. non-alphanumeric chars).
Returns local address of #wrapped.
Returns namespaces in scope for self – those defined on self element directly or any ancestor node – as a Hash of attribute-name/value pairs.
Returns namespaces in scope for self – those defined on self element directly or any ancestor node – as an Array of XML::Namespace objects.
Returns new Hash without nil values.
Returns only the values as an Array.
Returns request host from headers.
Returns request host with port from headers.
Returns self.
Returns the Socket::IPAddress with the determined port number.
Returns the #else of this case.
Returns the Char at the given index, or raises IndexError if out of bounds.
Returns the Float64 representing this rational.
Returns the Location representing the application's local time zone.
Returns the XML::Reader::Type of the node.
Returns the IPAddress for the local end of the IP socket.
Returns the IPAddress for the remote end of the IP socket.
Returns the #offset formatted as +HH:mm:ss.
Returns the #offset formatted as +HH:mm:ss. When with_colon is false, the format is +HHmmss.
Returns the whens of this case.
Returns the n-th subgroup in the most recent match.
Returns the quotient as absolutely negative if self and other have different signs, otherwise returns the quotient.
Returns the runtimeClass of an object.
Returns the HMAC digest of data using the secret key, formatted as a hexadecimal string.
Returns the HMAC digest of data using the secret key, formatted as a hexadecimal string. This is necessary to safely transfer the digest where binary messages are not allowed.
Returns the HMAC digest of data using the secret key.
Returns the ISO calendar year and week in which this instance occurs.
Returns the SI prefix for magnitude.
Returns the SSL context.
Returns the UTF-16 encoding of the given string.
Returns the XML for the node and its content including subtrees.
Returns the absolute (non-negative) amount of time this Time::Span represents by removing the sign.
Returns the absolute value of this complex number in a number form, using the Pythagorean theorem.
Returns the absolute value of this number.
Returns the address of this pointer.
Returns the address of underlying LibXML::Node* in memory.
Returns the anchor associated to the current event, or nil if there's no anchor.
Returns the appropriate equivalent hash algorithm that corresponds to the current enum value.
Returns the argument of the require.
Returns the argument types, or an empty list if no arguments.
Returns the arguments (the type variables) of this instantiation.
Returns the arguments of this macro.
Returns the arguments of this method.
Returns the arguments of this proc.
Returns the array of time zone offsets (Zone) used in this time zone.
Returns the base64-decoded version of data as a Bytes.
Returns the base64-decoded version of data as a Bytes. This will decode either the normal or urlsafe alphabets.
Returns the base64-decoded version of data as a string.
Returns the base64-decoded version of data as a string. This will decode either the normal or urlsafe alphabets.
Returns the base64-encoded hash of data.
Returns the base64-encoded version of data using a urlsafe alphabet.
Returns the base64-encoded version of data using a urlsafe alphabet. This method complies with "Base 64 Encoding with URL and Filename Safe Alphabet" in RFC 4648.
Returns the base64-encoded version of data with no newlines.
Returns the base64-encoded version of data with no newlines. This method complies with RFC 4648.
Returns the base64-encoded version of data.
Returns the base64-encoded version of data. This method complies with RFC 2045. Line feeds are added to every 60 encoded characters.
Returns the binary representation of the UUID.
Returns the block argument, if any.
Returns the block's body, if any.
Returns the block's value.
Returns the blocks arguments.
Returns the body of this when.
Returns the body of this macro.
Returns the body of this method.
Returns the body of this proc.
Returns the byte index of a char index, or nil if out of bounds.
Returns the bytes hold in the read buffer.
Returns the char index of a byte index, or nil if out of bounds.
Returns the class of this type.
Returns the class of this type. With this you can, for example, obtain class methods by invoking type.class.methods.
Returns the client Socket or nil if the server is closed after invoking this method.
Returns the client TCPSocket or nil if the server is closed after invoking this method.
Returns the client socket or nil if the server is closed after invoking this method.
Returns the client socket. Raises an IO::Error (closed stream) exception if the server is closed after invoking this method.
Returns the codepoint of this char.
Returns the column number where this node begins.
Returns the column number where this node begins. Might return nil if the location is not known.
Returns the column number where this node ends.
Returns the column number where this node ends. Might return nil if the location is not known.
Returns the components of this path as an Array(String).
Returns the concatenation of #drive and #root.
Returns the condition (target) of this case.
Returns the conditions of this when.
Returns the conjugate of self.
Returns the constants and types defined by this type.
Returns the content for this Node.
Returns the content for this Node. An empty string is returned if the node has no content.
Returns the content of filename as a string.
Returns the current Token.
Returns the current character.
Returns the current cipher used by this socket.
Returns the current modes set on the TLS context.
Returns the current nesting depth of the reader.
Returns the current options set on the TLS context.
Returns the current position (in bytes) in this IO.
Returns the current position (in bytes) in this IO.
Returns the current position (in bytes) of this IO.
Returns the current position of the scan offset.
Returns the current row as a Row instance.
Returns the current row's value at the given column index.
Returns the current row's value at the given column index. A negative index counts from the end. Raises IndexError if no such column exists.
Returns the current row's value at the given column index. A negative index counts from the end. Returns nil if no such column exists.
Returns the current row's value corresponding to the given header name.
Returns the current row's value corresponding to the given header name. Raises KeyError if no such header exists. Raises CSV::Error if headers were not requested.
Returns the current row's value corresponding to the given header name. Raises KeyError if no such header exists. Raises CSV::Error if headers were not requested.
Returns the current row's value corresponding to the given header name. Returns nil if no such header exists. Raises CSV::Error if headers were not requested.
Returns the current row's value corresponding to the given header_pattern.
Returns the current row's value corresponding to the given header_pattern. Raises KeyError if no such header exists. Raises CSV::Error if headers were not requested.
Returns the current row's value corresponding to the given header_pattern. Returns nil if no such header exists. Raises CSV::Error if headers were not requested.
Returns the current value of the hoplimit field on uni-cast packets.

Returns the current value of the hoplimit field on uni-cast packets. Datagrams with a hoplimit of 1 are not forwarded beyond the local network. Multicast datagrams with a hoplimit of 0 will not be transmitted on any network, but may be delivered locally if the sending host belongs to the destination group and multicast loopback is enabled.
Returns the current verify mode.
Returns the current verify mode. See the SSL_CTX_set_verify(3) manpage for more details.
Returns the current working directory.
Returns the day of the month (1..31).
Returns the day of the week (Monday..Sunday).
Returns the day of the year.
Returns the day of week that has the given value, or raises if no such member exists.
Returns the default port for the given scheme if known, otherwise returns nil.
Returns the default status description of the given HTTP status code.
Returns the default value of this argument, if any.
Returns the default value of this variable.

Returns the default value of this variable. Note that if the variable doesn't have a default value, or the default value is nil, a NilLiteral will be returned. To distinguish between these cases, use #has_default_value?.
Returns the difference of the codepoint values of self and other. The result is either negative, 0 or positive based on whether other's codepoint is less, equal, or greater than self's codepoint.
Returns the difference of the codepoint values of this char and other.
Returns the direct subclasses of this type.
Returns the direct superclass of this type.
Returns the double splat argument, if any.
Returns the downcase equivalent of this char.
Returns the duration between this Time and midnight of the same day.
Returns the elapsed real time used to execute the given block.
Returns the element at the given index or nil if out of bounds.
Returns the element at the given index or raises IndexError if out of bounds.
Returns the element at the given index or the value returned by the block if out of bounds.
Returns the element at the given index, if in bounds, otherwise executes the given block with the index and returns its value.
Returns the element at the given index, without doing any bounds check.
Returns the element at the given index.
Returns the element at the given index. Read the type docs to understand the difference between indexing with a number literal or a variable.
Returns the element for which the passed block returns with the maximum value.
Returns the element for which the passed block returns with the minimum value.
Returns the element with the maximum value in the collection.
Returns the element with the minimum value in the collection.
Returns the elements as an Array.
Returns the encoding of this node's document.
Returns the entry that has the given filename, or nil if no such entry exists.
Returns the entry that has the given filename, or raises KeyError if no such entry exists.
Returns the enum member that has the given name, or nil if no such member exists.

Returns the enum member that has the given name, or nil if no such member exists. The comparison is made by using String#camelcase and String#downcase between string and the enum members names, so a member named "FortyTwo" or "FORTY_TWO" is found with any of these strings: "forty_two", "FortyTwo", "FORTY_TWO", "FORTYTWO", "fortytwo".
Returns the enum member that has the given name, or raises ArgumentError if no such member exists.

Returns the enum member that has the given name, or raises ArgumentError if no such member exists. The comparison is made by using String#camelcase and String#downcase between string and the enum members names, so a member named "FortyTwo" or "FORTY_TWO" is found with any of these strings: "forty_two", "FortyTwo", "FORTY_TWO", "FORTYTWO", "fortytwo".
Returns the enum member that has the given value, or nil if no such member exists.
Returns the enum member that has the given value, or raises if no such member exists.
Returns the enum member that results from adding other to this enum member's value.
Returns the enum member that results from applying a logical "and" operation between this enum member's value and other.
Returns the enum member that results from applying a logical "and" operation between this enum member's value and other. This is mostly useful with flag enums.
Returns the enum member that results from applying a logical "not" operation of this enum member's value.
Returns the enum member that results from applying a logical "or" operation between this enum member's value and other.
Returns the enum member that results from applying a logical "or" operation between this enum member's value and other. This is mostly useful with flag enums.
Returns the enum member that results from applying a logical "xor" operation between this enum member's value and other.
Returns the enum member that results from applying a logical "xor" operation between this enum member's value and other. This is mostly useful with flag enums.
Returns the enum member that results from subtracting other to this enum member's value.
Returns the expression that the modifier is applied to.
Returns the expression that this unary operation is applied to.
Returns the extension of this path, or an empty string if it has no extension.
Returns the external name of this argument.
Returns the filename where this node is located.
Returns the filename where this node is located. Might return nil if the location is not known.
Returns the first n elements of the array.
Returns the first child node of this node that is an element.
Returns the first child node of this node that is an element. Returns nil if not found.
Returns the first element in the collection for which the passed block is true.
Returns the first element in the collection.
Returns the first element in the collection. Raises Enumerable::EmptyError if the collection is empty.
Returns the first element in the collection. When the collection is empty, returns nil.
Returns the first element of self if it's not empty, or nil.
Returns the first element of self if it's not empty, or raises IndexError.
Returns the first element of self if it's not empty, or the given block's value.
Returns the first element of this tuple, or nil if this is the empty tuple.
Returns the first element of this tuple.
Returns the first element of this tuple. Doesn't compile if the tuple is empty.
Returns the first header in the gzip stream, if any.
Returns the first key if it exists, or returns nil.
Returns the first key in the hash.
Returns the first value if it exists, or returns nil.
Returns the first value in the hash.
Returns the fragment component of the URI.
Returns the full path of this URI.
Returns the fully qualified name of this type.
Returns the given key value pairs as a url-encoded HTTP form/query.
Returns the greater of value1 and value2.
Returns the group associated with the given ID.
Returns the group associated with the given name.
Returns the hash of data.
Returns the hash of data. data must respond to #to_slice.
Returns the hexadecimal representation of the hash of data.
Returns the host component of the URI.
Returns the host part of the URI and unwrap brackets for IPv6 addresses.
Returns the hostname provided through Server Name Indication (SNI)
Returns the hostname.
Returns the hour of the day (0..23).
Returns the imaginary part.
Returns the index of search in the string, or nil if the string is not present.
Returns the index of search in the string, or nil if the string is not present. If offset is present, it defines the position to start the search.
Returns the index of the last appearance of search in the string, If offset is present, it defines the position to end the search (characters beyond this point are ignored).
Returns the index of the argument with a *splat, if any.
Returns the index of the first appearance of value in self starting from the given offset, or nil if the value is not in self.
Returns the index of the first element for which the passed block returns true.
Returns the index of the first object in self for which the block returns true, starting from the given offset, or nil if no match is found.
Returns the index of the first object in self for which the block returns true, starting from the last object, or nil if no match is found.
Returns the index of the given key, or nil when not found.
Returns the index of the given key, or nil when not found. The keys are ordered based on when they were inserted.
Returns the index of the last appearance of value in self, or nil if the value is not in self.
Returns the index of the object obj in the collection.
Returns the instance methods defined by this type, without including inherited methods.
Returns the instance type of this type, if it's a class type, or self otherwise.
Returns the instance type of this type, if it's a class type, or self otherwise. This is the opposite of #class.
Returns the instance variable used in this offsetof expression.
Returns the instance variables of this type.
Returns the integer value of this char as a float if it's an ASCII char denoting a digit, nil otherwise.
Returns the integer value of this char as a float if it's an ASCII char denoting a digit, raises otherwise.
Returns the integer value of this char if it's an ASCII char denoting a digit in base, nil otherwise.
Returns the integer value of this char if it's an ASCII char denoting a digit in base, raises otherwise.
Returns the internal buffer as a Pointer(UInt8).
Returns the internal name of this argument.
Returns the inverse of self.
Returns the keys in this named tuple type.
Returns the keys in this named tuple type. Gives a compile error if this is not a named tuple type.
Returns the last Annotation with the given #type attached to this variable or NilLiteral if there are none.
Returns the last Annotation with the given type attached to this variable or NilLiteral if there are none.
Returns the last n elements of the array.
Returns the last component of the given path.
Returns the last component of this path.
Returns the last element of self if it's not empty, or nil.
Returns the last element of self if it's not empty, or raises IndexError.
Returns the last element of self if it's not empty, or the given block's value.
Returns the last element of this tuple, or nil if this is the empty tuple.
Returns the last element of this tuple.
Returns the last element of this tuple. Doesn't compile if the tuple is empty.
Returns the last found element that was equal to obj, if any, or nil if not found.
Returns the last key if it exists, or returns nil.
Returns the last key in the hash.
Returns the last value if it exists, or returns nil.
Returns the last value in the hash.
Returns the left hand side of this node.
Returns the line number where this node begins.
Returns the line number where this node begins. Might return nil if the location is not known.
Returns the line number where this node ends.
Returns the line number where this node ends. Might return nil if the location is not known.
Returns the list of XML::Error found when parsing this document.
Returns the list of XML::Error found when parsing this document. Returns nil if no errors were found.
Returns the list of expressions in this node
Returns the logarithm of numeric to the base base.
Returns the mapping style, assuming the pull parser is located at a mapping begin event.
Returns the mapping style, assuming the pull parser is located at a mapping begin event. Raises otherwise.
Returns the match of the nth capture group, or nil if there isn't an nth capture group.
Returns the match of the nth capture group, or raises an IndexError if there is no nth capture group.
Returns the match of the capture group named by group_name, or nil if there is no such named capture group.
Returns the match of the capture group named by group_name, or raises an KeyError if there is no such named capture group.
Returns the maximum permitted combined size for the headers in an HTTP request.
Returns the maximum permitted size for the request line in an HTTP request.
Returns the memory in bytes that the given block consumes.
Returns the message of errno.
Returns the method name of this call.
Returns the method name that is being checked for.
Returns the millisecond of the second (0..999).
Returns the minute of the hour (0..59).
Returns the modified optval.
Returns the month of the year (1..12).
Returns the name for this Node.
Returns the name of the TLS protocol version used by this socket.
Returns the name of the instance variable being accessed.
Returns the name of the method this proc points to.
Returns the name of the node.
Returns the name of the zone.
Returns the name of this class.
Returns the name of this location.
Returns the name of this macro.
Returns the name of this method.
Returns the name of this variable.
Returns the named arguments of this instantiation, if any.
Returns the namespace for this node or nil if not found.
Returns the nanosecond of the second (0..999_999_999).
Returns the negotiated ALPN protocol (eg: "h2") of nil if no protocol was negotiated.
Returns the next Token in this CSV.
Returns the next character in the #string without incrementing #pos.
Returns the next character in the #string without incrementing #pos. Raises IndexError if the reader is at the end of the #string.
Returns the next element in this iterator, or Iterator::Stop::INSTANCE if there are no more elements.
Returns the next element node sibling or nil if not found.
Returns the next row in the CSV, if any, or nil.
Returns the next sibling node or nil if not found.
Returns the nilable n-th subgroup in the most recent match.
Returns the node's XML content including subtrees.
Returns the number 0 in complex form.
Returns the number of UTF-8 bytes in this char.
Returns the number of arguments of this Proc.
Returns the number of bytes in this string.
Returns the number of capture groups, including named capture groups.
Returns the number of columns in this row, regardless of the number of headers (if requested).
Returns the number of cookies contained in this collection.
Returns the number of days in month (value range: 1..12) taking account of the year.
Returns the number of days in year.
Returns the number of elements in the array.
Returns the number of elements in the collection for which the passed block returns true.
Returns the number of elements in the collection.
Returns the number of elements in the deque.
Returns the number of elements in the set.
Returns the number of elements in this Hash.
Returns the number of elements in this container.
Returns the number of elements in this match object.
Returns the number of elements in this named tuple.
Returns the number of elements in this tuple type or tuple metaclass type.
Returns the number of elements in this tuple type or tuple metaclass type. Gives a compile error if this is not one of those types.
Returns the number of elements in this tuple.
Returns the number of full days in this time span.
Returns the number of full hours of the day (0..23) in this time span.
Returns the number of full minutes of the hour (0..59) in this time span.
Returns the number of full seconds of the minute (0..59) in this time span.
Returns the number of full seconds.
Returns the number of leading 0-bits.
Returns the number of logical processors available to the system.
Returns the number of microseconds of the second (0..999999) in this time span.
Returns the number of milliseconds of the second (0..999) in this time span.

Second, allocate is a low-level class method that creates an uninitialized object of the given type. It basically allocates the necessary memory for the object, then initialize is invoked on it and finally the instance is returned. You generally never invoke allocate, as it is unsafe, but that's the reason why new and initialize are related.
